    {
      "hash": "b2cc9a6",
      "message": "debug: show visible error toast when item add fails on iPad\n\nRed toast at top of PosModal shows the actual error message\n(API failure, missing order, empty response) instead of only\nlogging to console which is invisible on iPad.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
      "date": "2026-03-15"
    },
    {
      "hash": "49dc7d4",
      "message": "fix: Clear Local Data now fully resets session\n\n- Broadened localStorage clear to include all air-pwa-* keys\n  (active PIN, menu cache, modifier cache) and device-settings\n- Unregisters service workers and clears SW caches\n- Reloads the page after clearing to reset all in-memory state\n  (order cache, menu data, modifier data, React state)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
      "date": "2026-03-15"
    },
    {
      "hash": "9f10d52",
      "message": "feat: quick-add items without required modifiers, add +mods link\n\n- handleItemTap now only shows ItemDetailSheet for items with\n  REQUIRED modifiers; all others quick-add directly to the order\n- Add modifierSelections to ItemDetailSheet handleAdd (was missing)\n- Add \"+mods\" link on order item rows (like \"+note\") to view/edit\n  modifiers on existing items via ItemDetailSheet in edit mode\n- Add updateItemModifiers to pos-store and API PATCH route\n- Network errors on modifier check now quick-add instead of blocking\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
      "date": "2026-03-15"
    },
    {
      "hash": "dbf5cb7",
      "message": "feat: iPad MenuGrid shows category picker grid before items\n\nWhen opening a table on iPad (PosModal → MenuGrid), show the same\n\"What are they having?\" category grid with emoji tiles that iPhone\nuses, instead of auto-selecting the first category. Adds search\nclear button and \"← All\" back navigation in category pills.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
      "date": "2026-03-15"
    },
    {
      "hash": "57bc417",
      "message": "feat: iPad category picker matches iPhone grid layout\n\nReplace the compact flex-wrap button list with a visual grid of\ncategory tiles showing emoji + name, matching the iPhone's\n\"What are they having?\" flow. Uses 4 columns (vs iPhone's 3)\nto take advantage of the wider iPad left panel.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
